The Alaska Volcano Observatory currently rates Mount Augustine as Level of Concern Color Code Green for aviation and the Volcano Alert Level is at Normal.
On January 17, 2006, Alaska Volcano Observatory recorded a strong seismic signal at 16:58 UTC lasting 5 minutes.
On January 28, 2006 the Alaska Volcano Observatory recorded explosive eruptions at 0524, 0837, 1104, and 1642 UTC. These eruptions had respective durations of 9, 1, 2, and 3 minutes.
